The filter object can be structured in one of two ways:

1. A simple filter: {field, operator, value}
2. A complex or nested filter: {logic, filters: [{field, operator, value}, ...]}


**Basic filter.**  
SAMPLE INPUT:

```
{
    field: "name",
    operator: "==",
    value: "Marta" 
}
```

**Logical OR, resolves to true if at least one of the conditions is true.**  
SAMPLE INPUT: 
```
{
  logic: "OR",
  filters: [
   { field: "active", operator: "==", value: false },
   { field: "name", operator: "==", value: "luis" },
  ]
}
```

**Logical AND, resolves to true if all of the conditions are true.**  
SAMPLE INPUT:
```
{
  logic: "AND",
  filters: [
   { field: "technology", operator: "==", value: "Firebase" },
   {
    logic: "OR",
    filters: [
     { field: "admin", operator: "==", value: true },
     { field: "age", operator: ">=", value: 18 },
    ],
   },
  ],
 }
```

**Filtering by references is also supported.**  
SAMPLE INPUT:
```
{
    field: "user_ref",
    operator: "==",
    value: "users/user123" 
}
```

